Author:  MCLEOD
Vol / Page:  110
Edition:
Quote:  Lambs which lose their mothers when they are young sometimes form an attachment for an inanimate object like a bush or rock and become what are known as 'hermits' sometimes called 'placer sheep.'
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1981
Source:  Loughnan Glossary
Author:  LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page:  41
Edition:
Quote:  Hermit: a sheep that has lost its gregarious nature and lives on its own. Quite often it was a motherless lamb which adopted a rock or a tree in loco parentis.
